==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prostitution
<hw>Pros`ti*tu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>prostitutio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>prostitution</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or practice of prostituting or offering the
body to an indiscriminate intercourse with men; common lewdness of a
woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of setting one's self to sale, or of
devoting to infamous purposes what is in one's power; <as>as, the
<ex>prostitution</ex> of abilities; the <ex>prostitution</ex> of the
press.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧Mental <xex>prostitution</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1152 --></p>

<p><ent>Prostitutor</ent>⟦br⟧
